1
00:00:09,030 --> 00:00:19,100
Timing and subtitles by the
🔔The Virtuoso🔔 Team @viki.com

2
00:00:21,204 --> 00:00:26,861
When I heard Mahler's symphony I felt chills.

3
00:00:26,861 --> 00:00:29,552
And I was truly curious...

4
00:00:29,552 --> 00:00:34,702
Who could conduct Mahler so beautifully like this?

5
00:00:34,702 --> 00:00:36,603
Who could this be?

6
00:00:39,189 --> 00:00:42,658
At worst it shouldn't
have been this old prick!

7
00:01:02,688 --> 00:01:09,461
I swear on my name
Franz von Stresemann.

8
00:01:09,461 --> 00:01:13,764
As long as I'm in charge of the
conducting major in this school

9
00:01:14,958 --> 00:01:16,893
Cha Yoo Jin...

10
00:01:19,329 --> 00:01:23,533
you will never be accepted
as a conducting major.

11
00:01:47,366 --> 00:01:50,749
[Lesson 3]

12
00:01:53,639 --> 00:01:55,379
Orabang!

13
00:02:07,493 --> 00:02:09,478
What's going on?

14
00:02:09,478 --> 00:02:11,465
Why did Yoo Jin storm out?

15
00:02:11,465 --> 00:02:14,801
Everyone in there is
untalented besides Yoo Jin.

16
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:16,787
Not just untalented..

17
00:02:16,787 --> 00:02:19,956
He excluded all of us, the elite. And
gathered all the losers in our school.

18
00:02:19,956 --> 00:02:22,859
All the losers are
gathered in there.

19
00:02:22,859 --> 00:02:25,695
Hi, everyone!

20
00:02:25,695 --> 00:02:30,299
Now we only have the leaders
of today remaining here.

21
00:02:31,234 --> 00:02:35,805
You are a special orchestra
that I selected personally.

22
00:02:35,805 --> 00:02:38,640
We're a family now.

23
00:02:39,642 --> 00:02:45,414
Orchestras are not built over night.

24
00:02:45,414 --> 00:02:49,100
We have to become a real family

25
00:02:49,100 --> 00:02:53,350
to create true harmony.

26
00:02:54,557 --> 00:03:02,330
The first step to our historic journey is...

27
00:03:11,025 --> 00:03:13,060
A dinner party!

28
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:23,720
Virtuosos are eccentric,
but he went too far.

29
00:03:23,720 --> 00:03:28,208
To be honest, there is no student
worthwhile without Yoo Jin.

30
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:31,781
He is a world-famous maestro. Trust him.

31
00:03:31,781 --> 00:03:37,118
He... must have a different plan.

32
00:03:41,555 --> 00:03:46,328
Orabang, I'll speak with
Milch about your transfer.

33
00:03:46,328 --> 00:03:48,088
We're really close!

34
00:03:48,088 --> 00:03:51,914
But if Yoo Jin transfers, you
can't play the piano with him.

35
00:03:51,914 --> 00:03:55,054
Disagree with your transfer!
Reject it! Don't leave me.

36
00:03:55,054 --> 00:03:56,545
Don't go!

37
00:03:56,545 --> 00:03:58,054
I want to be alone, so leave.

38
00:03:58,054 --> 00:04:01,390
What the heck?
Yoo Jin got rejected.

39
00:04:01,390 --> 00:04:03,759
We're best friends
whose souls are combined.

40
00:04:03,759 --> 00:04:06,442
We will never, ever be apart.

41
00:04:06,442 --> 00:04:08,512
What are you talking about!

42
00:04:08,512 --> 00:04:10,818
His lifetime partner is me!

43
00:04:10,818 --> 00:04:12,301
Hey, hey, Seol Nae Il!

44
00:04:12,301 --> 00:04:14,670
You shouldn't come between two men
and their bromance.

45
00:04:14,670 --> 00:04:17,306
That's not true! It's love over loyalty!

46
00:04:17,306 --> 00:04:19,241
Right, Orabang?

47
00:04:19,241 --> 00:04:23,112
- You must be so upset.
- Yoo Jin, cheer up.

48
00:04:23,112 --> 00:04:26,142
Both of you, get away from me!
You idiots!

49
00:04:32,063 --> 00:04:36,291
Orabang, this is Nae Il.
Please open the door.

50
00:04:36,291 --> 00:04:38,194
Do you think it'll open like that?

51
00:04:38,194 --> 00:04:40,162
Orabang!

52
00:04:41,573 --> 00:04:44,475
Orabang, open the door!

53
00:04:50,673 --> 00:04:53,875
What was the code
for Orabang's house?

54
00:04:54,543 --> 00:04:56,746
Could it be my birthday?

55
00:04:56,746 --> 00:05:01,646
Nae Il, is it better for
Yoo Jin to switch majors or not?

56
00:05:01,646 --> 00:05:07,469
I want to play piano with him,
I don't want things to change.

57
00:05:07,469 --> 00:05:11,293
But if he transfers, his
graduation would be delayed.

58
00:05:11,293 --> 00:05:15,163
He'd leave abroad, as soon as he graduates.

59
00:05:17,208 --> 00:05:19,736
What? Study abroad?

60
00:05:19,736 --> 00:05:22,204
Do you have anymore bad news?

61
00:05:22,204 --> 00:05:24,454
- What do I do...
- Why is she doing this to me?

62
00:05:24,454 --> 00:05:28,310
Orabang, are you going
to study abroad?

63
00:05:28,310 --> 00:05:32,014
Don't go abroad!
Stay here with me!

64
00:05:36,703 --> 00:05:38,604
Orabang...

65
00:05:51,977 --> 00:05:54,612
Yoo Jin! Yoo Jin!

66
00:05:59,870 --> 00:06:04,364
If I could just board a plane,
I wouldn't even be here!

67
00:06:04,364 --> 00:06:06,995
I can't go study abroad
or change my major.

68
00:06:06,995 --> 00:06:09,463
How am I supposed to learn to conduct?

69
00:06:13,489 --> 00:06:15,375
Who?

70
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:18,461
St... Stresemann?

71
00:06:20,196 --> 00:06:22,031
Is it Milch, Lak?

72
00:06:22,031 --> 00:06:26,386
Milch, please let Orabang change transfer!

73
00:06:26,386 --> 00:06:29,639
Our mascot is there as well?

74
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:32,267
Hey mascot, mascot!
Relax will you?

75
00:06:32,267 --> 00:06:36,955
- I'm sorry, but I can't go right now...
- Milch! Orabang's transfer!

76
00:06:36,955 --> 00:06:41,417
The concert master cannot miss this.

77
00:06:41,417 --> 00:06:44,220
Isn't it an important position

78
00:06:44,220 --> 00:06:47,489
as my assistant and my deputy?

79
00:06:51,734 --> 00:06:54,562
Lak, what's going on?
Where are you going?

80
00:06:54,562 --> 00:06:56,917
- We have to wait for Orabang.
- I'm sorry, Yoo Jin!

81
00:06:56,917 --> 00:06:59,817
Lak! Lak!

82
00:07:00,402 --> 00:07:02,123
Hey!

83
00:07:06,361 --> 00:07:07,962
Maestro...

84
00:07:09,763 --> 00:07:14,333
My son is the concertmaster...
I knew this day would come!

85
00:07:14,935 --> 00:07:17,272
He's an obvious choice.

86
00:07:17,272 --> 00:07:20,119
Of Course.

87
00:07:20,119 --> 00:07:23,151
He.. Has..

88
00:07:23,151 --> 00:07:26,205
You mean,
everyone has their place, right?

89
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:30,785
Yes. He fits this position perfectly.

90
00:07:30,785 --> 00:07:32,887
He deserves it.

91
00:07:34,997 --> 00:07:36,839
Father, what are you doing?

92
00:07:36,839 --> 00:07:38,977
My members are hungry.
Hurry, hurry!

93
00:07:38,977 --> 00:07:41,181
Okay, got it.

94
00:07:43,672 --> 00:07:47,217
I'll take care of your dinner tonight!

95
00:07:47,217 --> 00:07:51,387
Eat all you want! Nom, nom!

96
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:14,176
To S Orchestra, the Special Orchestra!

97
00:08:14,176 --> 00:08:16,945
Cheers!

98
00:08:33,780 --> 00:08:36,308
Beer is going in, beer is going in...

99
00:08:36,308 --> 00:08:38,702
Chug, chug, chug...

100
00:08:38,702 --> 00:08:41,839
How long will you make me wait?
Chug, chug, chug...

101
00:08:41,839 --> 00:08:46,480
Chug, chug, chug...

102
00:09:03,610 --> 00:09:06,645
If I could also express
this kind of music...

103
00:09:07,362 --> 00:09:09,401
If I could conduct...

104
00:09:25,948 --> 00:09:28,180
I'll wait for you here, Orabang.

105
00:09:28,180 --> 00:09:31,690
Call me anytime if you need anything.

106
00:09:31,690 --> 00:09:34,411
You'd do that much for me?

107
00:09:34,411 --> 00:09:36,810
I'm so moved.

108
00:09:36,810 --> 00:09:38,096
Orabang!

109
00:09:38,096 --> 00:09:40,013
Nae Il!

110
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:43,840
I love you.

111
00:10:04,220 --> 00:10:06,430
♫♫

112
00:10:36,950 --> 00:10:41,170
♫♫

113
00:10:41,170 --> 00:10:45,450
♫♫

114
00:10:45,450 --> 00:10:50,560
♫♫

115
00:11:10,622 --> 00:11:12,172
Hey, Nae Il!

116
00:11:12,172 --> 00:11:14,401
Orabang...

117
00:11:15,858 --> 00:11:18,526
Please give me a hug.

118
00:11:24,259 --> 00:11:26,261
I'm about to go crazy.

119
00:11:27,379 --> 00:11:29,247
It's warm here.

120
00:11:29,885 --> 00:11:31,353
Here.

121
00:11:36,446 --> 00:11:39,532
I know you have no ability to learn,
but don't go overboard.

122
00:11:39,532 --> 00:11:41,509
You'll catch a cold again.

123
00:11:41,509 --> 00:11:44,486
I thought you'd come out soon...

124
00:11:45,187 --> 00:11:47,023
Leave right after you eat.

125
00:11:47,023 --> 00:11:51,011
Can I stay here? I'll be quiet.

126
00:11:52,003 --> 00:11:54,514
Even if you stay quiet, no.

127
00:11:54,514 --> 00:11:58,051
I'll just stay in the corner
and breathe quietly.

128
00:11:58,051 --> 00:12:00,764
Nope, get out.

129
00:12:07,344 --> 00:12:09,845
I want to stay.

130
00:12:09,845 --> 00:12:11,773
I heard that a husband
and the wife are one.

131
00:12:11,773 --> 00:12:14,565
I won't go
anywhere leaving you behind.

132
00:12:15,818 --> 00:12:17,502
I said, I want to be alone!

133
00:12:17,502 --> 00:12:20,071
Why don't you listen to me!

134
00:12:22,625 --> 00:12:26,003
Honey, please don't do this.

135
00:12:26,003 --> 00:12:30,669
Let's try to make it work.
I'm here for you.

136
00:12:34,587 --> 00:12:36,388
You're right, Honey.

137
00:12:36,388 --> 00:12:40,191
I won't give up. I love you.

138
00:12:40,191 --> 00:12:42,457
Then they kiss each other...

139
00:12:42,457 --> 00:12:44,030
Honey...

140
00:12:44,662 --> 00:12:47,449
Then they got separated.

141
00:12:47,449 --> 00:12:48,919
No!

142
00:12:48,919 --> 00:12:52,114
No, you can't take him away!

143
00:12:52,114 --> 00:12:54,316
Give it back to me, you're evil!

144
00:12:54,316 --> 00:12:56,918
What will you do
if I give it back to you, pervert!

145
00:13:16,194 --> 00:13:17,862
My head...

146
00:13:22,267 --> 00:13:24,302
It smells, Professor.

147
00:13:24,302 --> 00:13:26,971
I came here to puke.

148
00:13:26,971 --> 00:13:28,807
It's not dirty.

149
00:13:28,807 --> 00:13:32,610
Su Min, you're my member.

150
00:13:33,230 --> 00:13:36,964
Maestro... von Stresemann...

151
00:13:38,984 --> 00:13:41,052
I love you...

152
00:13:41,052 --> 00:13:43,587
I love you too, Maestro!

153
00:13:43,587 --> 00:13:45,423
I love you...

154
00:13:46,992 --> 00:13:49,193
I love you!

155
00:14:22,671 --> 00:14:24,806
She's cute when she sleeps.

156
00:14:26,164 --> 00:14:27,617
What?

157
00:14:27,617 --> 00:14:30,135
Only when she's sleeping.
Everyone's cute while sleeping.

158
00:14:30,135 --> 00:14:32,636
I'm sure even a frog is
cute when it's sleeping.

159
00:14:34,806 --> 00:14:36,440
Am I crazy?

160
00:14:48,472 --> 00:14:50,285
Where are we?

161
00:14:51,517 --> 00:14:54,645
Oh, Orabang's home?

162
00:14:54,645 --> 00:14:59,483
Orabang, I'm hungry. Feed me.

163
00:15:02,734 --> 00:15:05,236
Hello, bunnies.

164
00:15:06,932 --> 00:15:08,173
What's this?

165
00:15:08,173 --> 00:15:10,175
Leave as soon as you wake up.

166
00:15:10,175 --> 00:15:12,677
Don't touch anything!

167
00:15:12,677 --> 00:15:16,414
Of course not,
I won't touch anything.

168
00:15:21,219 --> 00:15:24,555
My goodness, he's so cute.

169
00:15:27,325 --> 00:15:29,060
Finally!

170
00:15:35,133 --> 00:15:37,602
Yes.. Orabang's scent..

171
00:15:51,950 --> 00:15:54,919
I'm going to take this to Orabang!

172
00:16:04,690 --> 00:16:07,830
Are you okay?

173
00:16:14,846 --> 00:16:16,404
Do you want it?

174
00:16:16,404 --> 00:16:18,048
Really?

175
00:16:24,244 --> 00:16:27,945
Are they ruined?

176
00:16:29,813 --> 00:16:31,848
My goodness...

177
00:16:32,534 --> 00:16:34,614
Did it get dirty?

178
00:16:35,587 --> 00:16:37,688
Are you okay?

179
00:17:05,108 --> 00:17:08,044
- Do you want this, too?
- Thanks.

180
00:17:08,793 --> 00:17:11,729
I'll be late for class!

181
00:17:13,298 --> 00:17:16,133
- I can't help you carry it. I'm sorry.
- Don't worry.

182
00:17:20,749 --> 00:17:23,618
She must've been starving...

183
00:17:26,970 --> 00:17:30,347
What is this?
Who was it? Who did this?

184
00:17:38,934 --> 00:17:41,192
What the heck?

185
00:17:41,192 --> 00:17:42,860
Don't laugh!

186
00:17:42,860 --> 00:17:44,395
I thought it was odd
for a few days,

187
00:17:44,395 --> 00:17:46,965
but someone's determined
to bother me today.

188
00:17:46,965 --> 00:17:50,471
You have your way of getting attention.

189
00:17:50,471 --> 00:17:52,765
Yoo Jin still won't care at all.
Don't go overboard.

190
00:17:52,765 --> 00:17:53,972
I mean it, Lak!

191
00:17:53,972 --> 00:17:57,308
Someone must be jealous
of Yoo Jin and me.

192
00:17:57,308 --> 00:18:00,278
- I'm sure!
- Why don't you believe me?

193
00:18:00,278 --> 00:18:02,246
This is absolutely true..

194
00:18:16,594 --> 00:18:19,763
You're right. It must be true.

195
00:18:27,338 --> 00:18:30,207
These are conductor scores
I've been studying.

196
00:18:31,027 --> 00:18:33,397
Take a look, and then decide.

197
00:18:45,156 --> 00:18:47,628
I have many more.

198
00:18:47,628 --> 00:18:50,456
Process it once you change your mind.

199
00:19:00,905 --> 00:19:05,009
Do you know this man?

200
00:19:05,562 --> 00:19:07,356
He's my conducting mentor.

201
00:19:07,356 --> 00:19:08,507
Mentor?

202
00:19:08,507 --> 00:19:11,550
No wonder I didn't like you..

203
00:19:11,550 --> 00:19:15,000
You're a student my second most hated man..

204
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,454
What's that?

205
00:19:16,454 --> 00:19:18,823
[Toy store in London, 10 Years ago]

206
00:19:18,823 --> 00:19:21,926
You sold my toy to another customer.

207
00:19:21,926 --> 00:19:25,788
But it was reserved under my name.

208
00:19:25,788 --> 00:19:29,001
I apologize sir. Please, allow me
to make you another one.

209
00:19:29,001 --> 00:19:32,446
No, it's not the same!

210
00:19:32,446 --> 00:19:36,675
The one I want is a limited edition.

211
00:19:36,675 --> 00:19:38,776
The 'Birth of the Royal Baby'!

212
00:19:38,776 --> 00:19:44,333
I've been waiting for its
release for several months!

213
00:19:44,333 --> 00:19:46,549
Again sir, I am very sorry.

214
00:19:46,549 --> 00:19:49,153
But see, we had a very
famous customer come in.

215
00:19:49,153 --> 00:19:51,889
He made a special request
and an amazing offer.

216
00:19:51,889 --> 00:19:53,691
He even offered his autograph.

217
00:19:53,691 --> 00:19:56,259
I'm afraid we couldn't refuse.

218
00:19:56,259 --> 00:19:58,729
I'm famous, too!

219
00:19:59,364 --> 00:20:01,599
You don't look famous...

220
00:20:01,599 --> 00:20:03,668
And look, if you are going
to buy something, that's great.

221
00:20:03,668 --> 00:20:06,587
But if not, I'll have
to ask you to leave.

222
00:20:06,587 --> 00:20:08,293
Viera?

223
00:20:08,773 --> 00:20:10,986
Is that him?

224
00:20:12,613 --> 00:20:16,408
Excuse me, what are you doing?
No! No, no, no, no...

225
00:20:16,408 --> 00:20:19,544
If you are not going to buy
anything, just get out!

226
00:20:22,119 --> 00:20:25,422
- Because of that...
- 'Because of that'?

227
00:20:25,422 --> 00:20:29,454
I waited for several months to buy that.

228
00:20:29,454 --> 00:20:32,629
If that's all there was,
I could forgive.

229
00:20:33,464 --> 00:20:40,938
But you also look like
the person I hate the most.

230
00:20:41,873 --> 00:20:43,992
Leave.

231
00:20:43,992 --> 00:20:46,814
I'm not leaving
without the transfer.

232
00:20:46,814 --> 00:20:50,617
Fine, I'll give you a chance.

233
00:20:51,335 --> 00:20:55,155
- Give it your best shot.
- Pardon?

234
00:20:55,155 --> 00:21:00,293
Do you know the names of
the S Orchestra members?

235
00:21:02,721 --> 00:21:05,824
It's lunch time now, isn't it?

236
00:21:06,643 --> 00:21:12,615
Pass out lunch to
our hungry members.

237
00:21:12,615 --> 00:21:15,576
Don't miss anyone!

238
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:22,546
Make sure everyone eats
the food you prepared.

239
00:21:23,308 --> 00:21:26,276
It's 12 o'clock. Mission one!

240
00:21:26,884 --> 00:21:29,319
I will give you one hour.

241
00:21:49,407 --> 00:21:51,108
See? It's odd.

242
00:21:51,108 --> 00:21:54,779
He's been harassing me, and
now he's doing it to Orabang.

243
00:21:54,779 --> 00:21:58,051
- That's outlandish.
- No!

244
00:21:58,051 --> 00:22:00,384
Why'd he buy so many sandwiches?

245
00:22:00,384 --> 00:22:03,220
Right? But I still want one.

246
00:22:04,789 --> 00:22:06,356
Il Lak!

247
00:22:09,020 --> 00:22:11,363
Il Lak.

248
00:22:11,363 --> 00:22:14,542
Don't be mistaken.
We weren't following you, right?

249
00:22:14,542 --> 00:22:18,589
- What?
- We weren't watching you. We were on our way.

250
00:22:18,589 --> 00:22:21,692
- Okay, Lak. Let's go.
- Let's go.

251
00:22:22,607 --> 00:22:25,275
Hold it, hold it.

252
00:22:25,762 --> 00:22:28,656
Can you figure out
where S Orchestra members are?

253
00:22:28,656 --> 00:22:32,326
Of course! I'm Yoo Il Lak, the Great!

254
00:22:42,613 --> 00:22:45,490
- Come out, S Orchestra?
- Aren't they over there?

255
00:22:45,490 --> 00:22:47,828
Have a sandwich!

256
00:22:47,828 --> 00:22:49,076
Wait, wait!

257
00:22:49,076 --> 00:22:52,170
Il Lak, you go that way!
Nae Il, you go to the right!

258
00:22:52,170 --> 00:22:54,430
Spread out!

259
00:22:58,237 --> 00:23:01,546
Are you S Orchestra?
Are you S Orchestra? Get up!

260
00:23:01,546 --> 00:23:05,115
- Hurry, hurry!
- S Orchestra?

261
00:23:07,064 --> 00:23:09,832
Where did everyone go
during lunch hour?

262
00:23:09,832 --> 00:23:11,680
The cafeteria!

263
00:23:19,650 --> 00:23:21,569
Eat your sandwiches!

264
00:23:24,835 --> 00:23:28,405
- You're working hard.
- You too, Lak.

265
00:23:28,405 --> 00:23:29,250
Eat.

266
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:33,872
I'm full. I'm not going to eat it.

267
00:23:33,872 --> 00:23:35,446
- Nae Il!
- Yes?

268
00:23:35,446 --> 00:23:37,081
Come here.

269
00:23:37,960 --> 00:23:39,661
Please, Lak.

270
00:23:40,671 --> 00:23:43,473
You should eaten it
when we were being nice.

271
00:23:47,325 --> 00:23:49,693
Here, here!

272
00:23:51,329 --> 00:23:55,165
I gave lunch to all the members.

273
00:23:56,128 --> 00:24:00,203
So everyone received
lunch within the given time.

274
00:24:00,203 --> 00:24:03,100
Violin, viola, horn...

275
00:24:03,100 --> 00:24:06,036
Divided by the instrument...

276
00:24:06,036 --> 00:24:08,310
It's efficient.

277
00:24:12,101 --> 00:24:15,187
- One person is missing.
- Pardon?

278
00:24:15,187 --> 00:24:20,051
Our mascot, miss Seol Nae Il.

279
00:24:24,095 --> 00:24:26,930
Hey hey hey! Seol Nae Il!

280
00:24:27,632 --> 00:24:30,234
Milch! Please let him change his major!

281
00:24:30,234 --> 00:24:33,304
Why are you bothering
my Orabang? Why?

282
00:24:33,304 --> 00:24:35,806
Oh baby, you're mistaken.

283
00:24:35,806 --> 00:24:38,812
He's the one bothering me.

284
00:24:38,812 --> 00:24:41,848
- What did my Orabang do wrong?
- Seol Nae Il!

285
00:24:44,715 --> 00:24:46,817
I'll come back.

286
00:24:55,687 --> 00:24:58,207
I'm breaking up with you, Milch!

287
00:24:58,207 --> 00:25:00,411
We're not friends anymore!

288
00:25:00,411 --> 00:25:03,980
Oh baby, you're mistaken.

289
00:25:05,656 --> 00:25:07,257
Baby!

290
00:25:09,243 --> 00:25:11,637
Baby, it's a misunderstanding!

291
00:25:11,637 --> 00:25:14,205
I hate you, Milch!

292
00:25:14,205 --> 00:25:16,092
What's going on?

293
00:25:16,599 --> 00:25:18,744
I saw Yoo Jin leave.

294
00:25:18,744 --> 00:25:21,986
Was he rude, by any chance?

295
00:25:21,986 --> 00:25:24,588
He was, actually.

296
00:25:28,927 --> 00:25:30,294
Yoo Jin!

297
00:25:30,294 --> 00:25:32,407
Yoo Jin, you're a genius who tries hard.

298
00:25:32,407 --> 00:25:36,377
Orabang! Orabang, look at me.

299
00:25:36,377 --> 00:25:38,169
Lak, what are you doing?

300
00:25:38,169 --> 00:25:41,381
You have to let him be
alone at times like this.

301
00:25:41,381 --> 00:25:45,608
Look at me. I'm holding back
although I'm his best friend. Right?

302
00:25:49,158 --> 00:25:52,396
No! He needs consoling
in times like this.

303
00:25:52,396 --> 00:25:54,847
Orabang couldn't even eat lunch today.

304
00:25:54,847 --> 00:25:56,487
- What should I do?
- No no...

305
00:25:56,487 --> 00:25:57,955
Where do you think you're going?

306
00:25:57,955 --> 00:26:00,925
Move! What do you know, idiot!

307
00:26:00,925 --> 00:26:02,860
Nae Il! Nae Il!

308
00:26:02,860 --> 00:26:04,895
Tell Yoo Jin to give up
on changing his major!

309
00:26:04,895 --> 00:26:08,967
Can't you tell? He's never
going to let him transfer!

310
00:26:08,967 --> 00:26:10,988
What do you mean?

311
00:26:10,988 --> 00:26:13,667
What are you talking about?
Is he harassing Yoo Jin about transferring?

312
00:26:13,667 --> 00:26:15,324
How did you know?

313
00:26:15,324 --> 00:26:19,710
I could hear your loud voices
from down the street.

314
00:26:19,710 --> 00:26:21,878
Tell me now!

315
00:26:22,379 --> 00:26:24,715
- Von Stresemann?
- Yes.

316
00:26:24,715 --> 00:26:27,351
He was pulling a childish
prank on Yoo Jin

317
00:26:27,351 --> 00:26:31,008
with the possibility of
allowing him to change his major.

318
00:26:31,008 --> 00:26:33,124
Since it's the maestro's doing...

319
00:26:33,124 --> 00:26:34,992
Even as a maestro...

320
00:26:36,094 --> 00:26:38,182
He's gone too far.

321
00:26:38,763 --> 00:26:39,930
I'm surprised.

322
00:26:39,930 --> 00:26:43,367
Weren't you just about to expel
Yoo Jin from our school?

323
00:26:43,367 --> 00:26:46,736
Yes, and I still dislike him.

324
00:26:46,736 --> 00:26:48,973
He doesn't enter
into competitions with his skills.

325
00:26:48,973 --> 00:26:52,650
He does whatever he wants and doesn't
care about the school's reputation.

326
00:26:52,650 --> 00:26:54,907
Of course I don't like him.

327
00:26:54,907 --> 00:26:56,992
But this is different.

328
00:26:56,992 --> 00:27:01,096
Professors shouldn't mess with
a student's mind when he's willing to learn.

329
00:27:01,852 --> 00:27:06,256
By any chance...
did you allow this to happen?

330
00:27:08,259 --> 00:27:11,698
It was hard for us to get him here.
If we stay patient..

331
00:27:11,698 --> 00:27:13,766
Not, us.

332
00:27:14,932 --> 00:27:17,467
You brought him here.

333
00:27:20,070 --> 00:27:23,173
I don't know if I can trust
you as our dean anymore.

334
00:27:24,308 --> 00:27:26,610
I'll be watching you as well.

335
00:27:26,610 --> 00:27:28,378
Excuse me.

336
00:27:40,157 --> 00:27:42,192
Orabang...

337
00:27:48,959 --> 00:27:51,836
Orabang, I broke up with Milch.

338
00:27:51,836 --> 00:27:54,238
I'll never hang out with him again.

339
00:27:54,238 --> 00:27:57,040
You must've been really upset.

340
00:27:58,095 --> 00:28:01,698
By any chance...
is someone bothering you these days?

341
00:28:03,307 --> 00:28:07,409
God is. God is punishing me.

342
00:28:07,409 --> 00:28:10,355
I deserve it.

343
00:28:10,355 --> 00:28:14,014
I'm the mascot of S Orchestra...

344
00:28:14,014 --> 00:28:17,427
Sure, I forgot that too.

345
00:28:18,115 --> 00:28:20,709
Is it because my brain
is rejecting the fact?

346
00:28:20,709 --> 00:28:24,137
Orabang, you need to eat
better in times like this.

347
00:28:24,137 --> 00:28:27,164
I prepared this lunchbox myself.

348
00:28:27,164 --> 00:28:30,066
Seol Nae Il's love lunchbox!

349
00:28:32,863 --> 00:28:34,690
Are you kidding me?

350
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:38,575
Whoever it is, he
knows your every move.

351
00:28:41,553 --> 00:28:43,587
I will.. Kill him.

352
00:28:43,587 --> 00:28:45,767
You dare to touch my lunchbox?

353
00:28:45,767 --> 00:28:50,367
Especially the love lunchbox
that I prepared for my Orabang?

354
00:28:50,367 --> 00:28:52,769
I won't let it slide.

355
00:28:55,861 --> 00:28:57,719
Lak, it's me. Let's meet right now.

356
00:28:57,719 --> 00:29:00,180
It's time for revenge!

357
00:29:00,180 --> 00:29:01,767
Right now!

358
00:29:01,767 --> 00:29:04,102
I'm going to take my revenge!

359
00:29:07,811 --> 00:29:11,114
She's not afraid of God when it comes to food.

360
00:29:37,294 --> 00:29:38,787
Got you!

361
00:29:38,787 --> 00:29:42,224
- Hey, Nae Il!
- You stole my lunchbox!

362
00:29:43,116 --> 00:29:45,944
- What? What?
- Search his backpack!

363
00:29:45,944 --> 00:29:47,100
I'm going to check!

364
00:29:50,874 --> 00:29:52,958
Where is it?

365
00:29:56,547 --> 00:29:58,148
What's this?

366
00:30:01,635 --> 00:30:04,170
These are pictures of me...

367
00:30:06,515 --> 00:30:11,275
I'm sorry. I have someone
I promised to marry.

368
00:30:11,275 --> 00:30:12,943
It's not going to happen for us.

369
00:30:12,943 --> 00:30:15,446
God Almighty Cha is not
interested in you anyway!

370
00:30:15,446 --> 00:30:17,247
God Almighty Cha?

371
00:30:17,247 --> 00:30:19,249
This...

372
00:30:20,179 --> 00:30:22,286
This is... Yoo Jin.

373
00:30:22,286 --> 00:30:24,867
It's Orabang...

374
00:30:24,867 --> 00:30:27,061
Excuse me, Orabang is a guy...

375
00:30:27,061 --> 00:30:30,093
So what? People still have feelings.

376
00:30:30,093 --> 00:30:33,896
Right? People still have feelings.

377
00:30:33,896 --> 00:30:36,353
Aren't you... Ma Su Min?

378
00:30:36,353 --> 00:30:37,970
Right? Take off your sunglasses.

379
00:30:37,970 --> 00:30:40,939
- Take off your sunglasses!
- No!

380
00:30:42,509 --> 00:30:44,511
It's him, right?

381
00:30:45,235 --> 00:30:47,371
Is he someone you know, Lak?

382
00:30:47,371 --> 00:30:49,806
He plays timpani for our S Orchestra.

383
00:31:21,945 --> 00:31:23,280
This is foul play.

384
00:31:23,280 --> 00:31:29,018
I can't even get mad at you about
two-timing us and joining S Orchestra.

385
00:31:30,988 --> 00:31:33,123
Do you want a piece of cake?
You must be hungry.

386
00:31:33,123 --> 00:31:37,127
I like Yoo Jin.

387
00:31:41,135 --> 00:31:43,276
Like I didn't know...

388
00:31:43,276 --> 00:31:45,305
When you make it that obvious,
who wouldn't know?

389
00:31:45,305 --> 00:31:46,949
I'm sure everyone else knows, too.

390
00:31:46,949 --> 00:31:50,219
Your eyes follow Yoo Jin
whenever you see him.

391
00:31:51,662 --> 00:31:54,323
Which one? Cheese? Chocolate?

392
00:31:54,323 --> 00:31:56,254
Cheesecake.

393
00:31:56,900 --> 00:31:59,878
Don't you... find me weird?

394
00:31:59,878 --> 00:32:03,814
I like Hyuna. And I love Yuna.

395
00:32:04,858 --> 00:32:06,892
Does that make me odd?

396
00:32:07,386 --> 00:32:11,094
Whether it's a person or music,
as long as you like it, it's fine.

397
00:32:11,094 --> 00:32:13,797
Your heart follows what you like.
What can you do?

398
00:32:21,858 --> 00:32:24,595
Wow, I didn't think Su Min
would be that way, but he's scary.

399
00:32:24,595 --> 00:32:26,877
Throwing banana peels and
shooting an arrow...

400
00:32:26,877 --> 00:32:28,989
Switching lunch boxes and
even throwing water!

401
00:32:28,989 --> 00:32:32,310
It means he followed you
all day to harass you!

402
00:32:32,310 --> 00:32:36,167
When you like someone,
can you go crazy like that?

403
00:32:36,167 --> 00:32:38,561
He didn't have anyone to be
jealous, he was jealous of you?

404
00:32:38,561 --> 00:32:41,529
Now I think about it,
it's not even funny.

405
00:32:41,529 --> 00:32:44,559
This is why I don't date anyone!

406
00:32:44,559 --> 00:32:47,984
It turns a perfectly normal
person into an idiot in a second.

407
00:32:47,984 --> 00:32:51,386
Nae Il, rather than
wasting my emotions like that

408
00:32:51,386 --> 00:32:54,815
I'm going to throw my body
into classical music,

409
00:32:54,815 --> 00:32:57,383
the essence of
innocent soul and mind.

410
00:32:58,275 --> 00:32:59,573
Lak...

411
00:32:59,573 --> 00:33:01,378
Yes? What?

412
00:33:01,378 --> 00:33:04,648
You don't know the greatness of love...

413
00:33:04,648 --> 00:33:07,350
You're always an idiot.

414
00:33:07,918 --> 00:33:09,858
Bye now.

415
00:33:11,789 --> 00:33:13,623
Love...

416
00:33:14,625 --> 00:33:17,060
What's wrong with her now?

417
00:33:17,871 --> 00:33:20,017
Milch, wait!

418
00:33:22,132 --> 00:33:23,734
Please, Milch!

419
00:33:23,734 --> 00:33:27,270
We're friends, best friends!

420
00:33:27,270 --> 00:33:30,505
Let Orabang change his major!

421
00:33:32,743 --> 00:33:35,579
Or let him conduct just once.

422
00:33:35,579 --> 00:33:38,081
Then you'll change your mind.

423
00:33:38,081 --> 00:33:42,352
When you do this, baby,
it hurts my heart.

424
00:33:42,352 --> 00:33:44,521
Then give Orabang a chance!

425
00:33:44,521 --> 00:33:46,466
He...

426
00:33:47,509 --> 00:33:49,888
He doesn't have enough
virtue to conduct.

427
00:33:49,888 --> 00:33:53,023
But you conduct, Milch!

428
00:33:56,186 --> 00:33:59,105
No matter what you say...

429
00:33:59,105 --> 00:34:00,571
I can't allow it!

430
00:34:00,571 --> 00:34:04,270
Milch! Milch, please listen to me.

431
00:34:04,270 --> 00:34:07,710
Orabang will do great!

432
00:34:07,710 --> 00:34:10,186
Where are you going?

433
00:34:30,134 --> 00:34:31,931
Orabang!

434
00:34:31,931 --> 00:34:35,161
Orabang, let's go! Hurry!

435
00:34:37,060 --> 00:34:38,892
Where are we going?

436
00:34:51,383 --> 00:34:56,285
Today our Orabang will be conducting.

437
00:34:56,285 --> 00:34:58,568
Milch...

438
00:34:59,416 --> 00:35:02,978
I mean, the professor left
conducting to Orabang.

439
00:35:02,978 --> 00:35:04,379
What?

440
00:35:16,033 --> 00:35:19,869
Here's a baton,
and the conductor score.

441
00:35:20,644 --> 00:35:22,366
Do I...

442
00:35:22,366 --> 00:35:24,566
really get to conduct?

443
00:35:24,566 --> 00:35:26,757
I'm really about to do this?

444
00:35:26,757 --> 00:35:29,325
Can you even read
conductor scores??

445
00:35:30,231 --> 00:35:32,948
Sure, I've done it.

446
00:35:32,948 --> 00:35:35,867
He's been studying hard
this whole time.

447
00:35:35,867 --> 00:35:39,931
Even our professor trusted him.
He must have a good reason.

448
00:35:39,931 --> 00:35:42,626
As our bandmaster,
I welcome you, Cha Yoo Jin.

449
00:35:42,626 --> 00:35:44,207
Bandmaster?

450
00:35:44,207 --> 00:35:48,378
Assistant to the conductor
as well as the first chair violinist?

451
00:35:48,378 --> 00:35:50,847
Yeah, that's me.

452
00:35:53,884 --> 00:35:58,054
It's Beethoven Symphony No.3.

453
00:36:01,448 --> 00:36:02,793
Have you all practiced?

454
00:36:02,793 --> 00:36:07,663
Of course, we decided on that
song during our last meeting.

455
00:36:16,740 --> 00:36:19,409
Beethoven Symphony No. 3, Eroica.

456
00:36:19,409 --> 00:36:23,498
A song that portrays great
spirit and strong personality..

457
00:36:23,498 --> 00:36:29,957
How would von Stresemann's
orchestra show a hero's melody?

458
00:36:34,551 --> 00:36:35,910
Please come out now.

459
00:36:35,910 --> 00:36:38,891
How were these moved here?

460
00:36:38,891 --> 00:36:40,951
That's the power of love.

461
00:36:40,951 --> 00:36:43,620
He even has luck with the ladies.

462
00:36:49,918 --> 00:36:54,255
You thief! Using a woman
to steal my baton?

463
00:36:55,724 --> 00:36:58,326
You're finished!

464
00:36:59,983 --> 00:37:02,873
My first orchestra.

465
00:37:02,873 --> 00:37:05,174
My first chance as a conductor...

466
00:37:16,032 --> 00:37:18,134
It's the worst!

467
00:37:36,907 --> 00:37:39,742
How can you call this an orchestra?

468
00:37:41,036 --> 00:37:42,679
That old jerk!

469
00:37:42,679 --> 00:37:46,415
He just put together
the worst musicians!

470
00:38:02,683 --> 00:38:06,205
Do a better job! It's the first time,
but still, you should put more effort!

471
00:38:06,205 --> 00:38:09,686
Play Eroica in a majestic, imposing way.

472
00:38:09,686 --> 00:38:11,788
Pour your soul into it...

473
00:38:11,788 --> 00:38:14,658
- Bandmaster.
- Yes, Bandmaster Yoo Il Lak!

474
00:38:14,658 --> 00:38:16,680
You're the problem.

475
00:38:16,680 --> 00:38:18,753
You're making mistakes constantly.

476
00:38:18,753 --> 00:38:20,425
Second violin.

477
00:38:20,425 --> 00:38:22,300
Are you sure you're a music student?

478
00:38:22,300 --> 00:38:23,780
Second horn!

479
00:38:23,780 --> 00:38:26,235
Don't cut off on a long fortissimo!

480
00:38:26,235 --> 00:38:27,937
Second clarinet.

481
00:38:27,937 --> 00:38:30,305
You're off tune.

482
00:38:30,305 --> 00:38:31,993
Viola.

483
00:38:31,993 --> 00:38:33,975
You're too loud by yourself.

484
00:38:34,381 --> 00:38:35,871
Timpani!

485
00:38:38,441 --> 00:38:40,542
Just manage your excitement.

486
00:38:44,272 --> 00:38:48,943
After a 10-minute break,
we'll start from the beginning again.

487
00:38:54,443 --> 00:38:57,112
He's so sexy when he gets mad.

488
00:39:22,057 --> 00:39:23,774
Second clarinet!

489
00:39:23,774 --> 00:39:25,460
I told you not to cut notes short!

490
00:39:25,460 --> 00:39:28,111
Second horn. You're out of tune.

491
00:39:28,111 --> 00:39:31,738
Cello... How many times
have I told you that you're flat!

492
00:39:32,274 --> 00:39:36,014
Viola... I told you that
you're too loud by yourself.

493
00:39:40,739 --> 00:39:43,033
Orabang is talented.

494
00:39:43,033 --> 00:39:46,169
He can hear everyone individually.

495
00:39:51,959 --> 00:39:53,576
Milch!

496
00:40:13,396 --> 00:40:18,935
Enjoying yourself with my stolen baton
and conductor scores?

497
00:40:20,420 --> 00:40:23,589
How should I punish you?

498
00:40:23,626 --> 00:40:27,295
How dare you pull something like this.

499
00:40:27,295 --> 00:40:30,159
Orabang, I'm sorry.

500
00:40:30,159 --> 00:40:35,163
Milch, I did this.
Orabang didn't do anything.

501
00:40:39,815 --> 00:40:44,215
I'll appoint Yoo Jin...

502
00:40:47,064 --> 00:40:50,183
as my assistant conductor for a week.

503
00:40:51,577 --> 00:40:55,206
I'll give you a chance, to try it.

504
00:40:55,206 --> 00:40:57,667
If you fail after a week,
you are done here,

505
00:40:57,667 --> 00:41:00,970
and no more transfer requests.

506
00:41:00,970 --> 00:41:02,818
Is that a deal?

507
00:41:02,818 --> 00:41:04,779
Do we have a deal?

508
00:41:07,509 --> 00:41:10,069
- You don't want to?
- Yes, I will.

509
00:41:10,069 --> 00:41:14,173
I'll create a beautiful performance.

510
00:41:42,438 --> 00:41:47,774
Orabang! Congratulations on becoming
the assistant conductor!

511
00:41:47,774 --> 00:41:49,319
I see what you're doing!

512
00:41:49,319 --> 00:41:51,287
I told you that you're
forbidden to touch me.

513
00:41:52,279 --> 00:41:54,723
Your defense is iron-clad.

514
00:41:54,723 --> 00:41:58,426
Clumsy guys are more popular
these days.

515
00:42:01,283 --> 00:42:02,881
I see a hole! In your defense!

516
00:42:02,881 --> 00:42:04,482
Here.

517
00:42:07,236 --> 00:42:12,674
Orabang!

518
00:42:12,674 --> 00:42:14,381
Don't follow me!

519
00:42:15,786 --> 00:42:17,201
Orabang...

520
00:42:17,201 --> 00:42:20,034
[The Orchestra Autumn Concert]

521
00:42:22,665 --> 00:42:26,609
Orabang, I put a lot of
effort to prepare this for you!

522
00:42:26,609 --> 00:42:32,508
Your favorite, curry tuna!

523
00:42:32,508 --> 00:42:35,347
Just pour it over the rice.

524
00:42:41,550 --> 00:42:43,794
Orabang, don't you know
table manners?

525
00:42:43,794 --> 00:42:45,815
When your meal is ready...

526
00:42:51,133 --> 00:42:53,443
I'll keep my mouth shut.

527
00:43:10,507 --> 00:43:15,891
I prepared an analysis for each
individual instrument. It'll be helpful.

528
00:43:15,891 --> 00:43:19,322
He's definitely a genius.
Everything's perfect.

529
00:43:19,322 --> 00:43:22,853
You're more than qualified to become
the best friend of Bandmaster Yoo Il Lak.

530
00:43:22,853 --> 00:43:26,669
Everyone, do your best! Okay?

531
00:43:26,669 --> 00:43:29,504
Talk for yourself!

532
00:43:31,278 --> 00:43:32,846
Let's start.

533
00:43:42,981 --> 00:43:44,666
Hello.

534
00:43:44,666 --> 00:43:47,081
- You don't need to bow.
- Okay.

535
00:43:47,081 --> 00:43:49,196
I saw the post for a part-time job.

536
00:43:49,196 --> 00:43:53,762
Isn't it heavy? You can get
a hard case with wheels.

537
00:43:53,762 --> 00:43:57,633
It's broken,
I can't afford to fix it..

538
00:43:57,633 --> 00:44:00,416
I saw the post for a part-time job.

539
00:44:00,416 --> 00:44:02,309
Oh, yes. It's the cashier's position.

540
00:44:02,309 --> 00:44:04,853
It's from five to eleven, and the
pay is as written on the post.

541
00:44:04,853 --> 00:44:06,227
Thank you!

542
00:44:06,227 --> 00:44:07,776
- Don't bow...
- Okay.

543
00:44:07,776 --> 00:44:09,678
Why don't you leave it
and rest for now?

544
00:44:09,678 --> 00:44:11,780
I have to go straight to school.

545
00:44:11,780 --> 00:44:14,992
I'll be back by five.

546
00:44:14,992 --> 00:44:16,785
See you later.

547
00:44:23,997 --> 00:44:25,495
Be careful!

548
00:45:23,545 --> 00:45:25,038
Two shots of espresso, please.

549
00:45:25,038 --> 00:45:28,240
That'll ruin your stomach.
Just drink fruit tea from now on.

550
00:45:35,043 --> 00:45:37,691
Is this really the only way
I can meet my son?

551
00:45:37,691 --> 00:45:39,594
Why didn't you text back?

552
00:45:39,594 --> 00:45:41,929
You know I don't check my phone.

553
00:45:42,868 --> 00:45:46,028
By the way, why does it have
to be in front of my school?

554
00:45:46,028 --> 00:45:48,040
Because I want to be close to my son.

555
00:45:48,040 --> 00:45:50,267
You should've given me that
attention when I was little.

556
00:45:50,267 --> 00:45:51,727
I was busy then.

557
00:45:51,727 --> 00:45:54,820
But now you can have
my full attention.

558
00:45:54,820 --> 00:45:58,033
No thanks. Now I'm busy.

559
00:45:58,033 --> 00:46:00,244
You must be really busy.

560
00:46:00,244 --> 00:46:02,287
Aren't you eating well?
Why are you so skinny?

561
00:46:02,287 --> 00:46:04,526
You're better at
cooking than I am.

562
00:46:04,526 --> 00:46:07,736
It's just... a bit strange.

563
00:46:07,736 --> 00:46:09,144
Huh?

564
00:46:09,144 --> 00:46:12,103
I'm following the conductor's score...

565
00:46:12,103 --> 00:46:15,103
'Delicate, powerful and bold'...

566
00:46:15,103 --> 00:46:17,113
I'm following that...

567
00:46:18,654 --> 00:46:22,023
I guess one week is not enough?

568
00:46:22,023 --> 00:46:25,277
Are you even eating?

569
00:46:27,663 --> 00:46:29,497
I'll come back another time.

570
00:46:34,869 --> 00:46:37,297
Okay, come when you feel like it.

571
00:46:37,297 --> 00:46:38,680
Bye.

572
00:46:48,892 --> 00:46:52,911
Hello, Professor. I'm Jang Shi Won,
orchestra concert mistress.

573
00:46:52,911 --> 00:46:56,633
Nice to meet you, Shi Won.
Bye now.

574
00:46:56,633 --> 00:46:59,762
I'd like to discuss
our practice schedule, Professor.

575
00:46:59,762 --> 00:47:04,280
Oh, S Orchestra Concertmaster Il Lak is coming.

576
00:47:04,280 --> 00:47:09,187
Discuss anything about practice with him.

577
00:47:09,187 --> 00:47:10,859
Professor, our practice...

578
00:47:10,859 --> 00:47:13,164
Hi, I'm Jang Shi Won.

579
00:47:13,164 --> 00:47:15,460
The concert mistress of
our school orchestra.

580
00:47:15,460 --> 00:47:17,838
Ah, that Jang Shi Won!

581
00:47:17,838 --> 00:47:20,145
It looks like Professor
left it all to you.

582
00:47:20,145 --> 00:47:21,770
Tell me the practice schedule.

583
00:47:21,770 --> 00:47:24,506
And the professor's style
and choice of music, too.

584
00:47:24,506 --> 00:47:26,469
Oh, and anything else of note?

585
00:47:26,469 --> 00:47:27,870
I don't know because
we haven't practiced together.

586
00:47:27,870 --> 00:47:29,305
We're not rivals,
so why are you hiding things?

587
00:47:29,305 --> 00:47:31,168
I really don't know.

588
00:47:31,168 --> 00:47:33,815
Yoo Jin became the assistant
conductor on the first day.

589
00:47:33,815 --> 00:47:35,881
Pianist Cha Yoo Jin?

590
00:47:35,881 --> 00:47:38,020
He's my best friend...

591
00:47:38,020 --> 00:47:41,069
'Birds of a feathers flock together.'
He can do everything well, just like me.

592
00:47:41,069 --> 00:47:43,798
- A piano major is conducting?
- Yes!

593
00:47:45,032 --> 00:47:46,617
You should at least make an effort
if you're going to lie to me.

594
00:47:46,617 --> 00:47:51,020
It's true!
Why don't you believe me?

595
00:47:58,962 --> 00:48:01,839
Did she already pass by?

596
00:48:01,839 --> 00:48:05,580
I didn't get to see her once today.

597
00:48:05,580 --> 00:48:08,503
Who are you looking for?

598
00:48:24,488 --> 00:48:29,034
I wonder if I dragged you away
from your busy schedule.

599
00:48:29,034 --> 00:48:35,466
I've been busy this whole time,
but I happened to be free now.

600
00:48:35,466 --> 00:48:37,639
I'm glad.

601
00:48:37,639 --> 00:48:43,439
To be honest, I want to know
what's really on your mind, Franz.

602
00:48:44,424 --> 00:48:48,207
What? What's on my mind?

603
00:48:51,165 --> 00:48:56,889
Why do you want to know?

604
00:48:58,005 --> 00:49:01,776
I'm sorry, I'm speaking as the dean.

605
00:49:01,776 --> 00:49:07,014
To be honest,
I invited you for our orchestra.

606
00:49:07,014 --> 00:49:09,949
But I hear you don't pay
much attention to them.

607
00:49:11,852 --> 00:49:15,717
- Han Eum is also my orchestra.
- I know.

608
00:49:15,717 --> 00:49:20,589
Of course, I thank you
for creating a special orchestra.

609
00:49:20,589 --> 00:49:24,965
But I'd like to know your plan, Franz.

610
00:49:24,965 --> 00:49:29,803
Do you think
I will let you down, Mina?

611
00:49:30,885 --> 00:49:33,804
Did I put you in an awkward
position, by any chance?

612
00:49:33,804 --> 00:49:40,742
Of course not. I guess I said nonsense out of concern.

613
00:49:42,110 --> 00:49:45,140
Isn't the campus really pretty?

614
00:49:45,140 --> 00:49:48,678
The campus is beautiful this season.

615
00:49:48,678 --> 00:49:50,746
How pretty...

616
00:50:05,422 --> 00:50:08,267
If you have nothing more to say...

617
00:50:08,267 --> 00:50:10,150
To be honest...

618
00:50:11,595 --> 00:50:14,513
I have a personal favor to ask.

619
00:50:17,479 --> 00:50:21,313
Yoo Jin is a very talented student.

620
00:50:21,313 --> 00:50:23,482
Please take good care of him.

621
00:50:35,536 --> 00:50:40,766
Dean, I hear you created
another orchestra?

622
00:50:40,766 --> 00:50:43,268
It was von Stresemann's request.

623
00:50:43,710 --> 00:50:45,713
We don't have the funds.

624
00:50:45,713 --> 00:50:48,617
There is a limit to how much
we can get from contributions.

625
00:50:48,617 --> 00:50:51,085
There you go again, Professor Do.

626
00:50:51,085 --> 00:50:54,026
You shouldn't connect
education with money.

627
00:50:55,681 --> 00:50:58,699
You must have a plan, Dean?

628
00:50:58,699 --> 00:51:02,710
Additional profit from video exposure...

629
00:51:04,147 --> 00:51:07,109
Maestro von Stresemann avoids
contact with the media.

630
00:51:07,109 --> 00:51:09,931
Does he have something to hide?

631
00:51:09,931 --> 00:51:13,448
The people will be suspicious of
his actions.

632
00:51:13,448 --> 00:51:15,909
He's a very eccentric man.

633
00:51:15,909 --> 00:51:20,778
He must be, if he created a new
orchestra in spite of our Han Eum.

634
00:51:23,472 --> 00:51:27,143
Include both orchestras
in the autumn concert.

635
00:51:27,143 --> 00:51:29,812
I'll decide afterwards.

636
00:51:36,305 --> 00:51:39,220
How many times do I have
to tell you, idiots!

637
00:51:39,220 --> 00:51:40,762
I think he's gone mad..

638
00:51:40,762 --> 00:51:42,349
He's a tyrant!

639
00:51:42,349 --> 00:51:45,860
I hate it when girls look at Orabang...

640
00:51:47,274 --> 00:51:50,210
I hate it more
when they talk bad about him.

641
00:51:50,679 --> 00:51:52,526
Contrabass.

642
00:51:52,526 --> 00:51:55,247
You stick out alone and
mess up the rhythm.

643
00:51:57,075 --> 00:51:58,776
We have one day left.

644
00:51:59,593 --> 00:52:04,097
It's tomorrow, but we are sounding worse.
Do you understand?

645
00:52:06,919 --> 00:52:10,013
Even when Yoo Jin is being a tyrant,

646
00:52:10,013 --> 00:52:12,115
the girls still like him.

647
00:52:12,687 --> 00:52:14,644
Don't they have brains?

648
00:52:14,644 --> 00:52:16,524
They don't have pride.

649
00:52:17,012 --> 00:52:20,431
'It's okay to get angry...
as long as you have a pretty face.'

650
00:52:20,431 --> 00:52:23,367
Hey, you're better if it's face alone.

651
00:52:25,373 --> 00:52:28,357
But your height comes up a bit short.

652
00:52:28,357 --> 00:52:32,894
True, your body alone's pretty good, too.
Clothes look good on you.

653
00:52:37,205 --> 00:52:38,539
Hey...

654
00:52:39,239 --> 00:52:42,621
Should we pull a prank on Yoo Jin?

655
00:52:42,621 --> 00:52:44,892
So that he'll never
be a stuck-up again.

656
00:52:51,880 --> 00:52:53,391
Aren't you going to focus?

657
00:52:53,882 --> 00:52:56,601
Why is it sounding worse?

658
00:53:05,139 --> 00:53:09,751
Switch the oboe and the clarinet
when it's really hard to notice.

659
00:53:09,751 --> 00:53:13,656
Yoo Jin will never notice it.
Let's embarrass him.

660
00:53:13,656 --> 00:53:15,257
Again.

661
00:54:05,887 --> 00:54:09,882
You've been lazy,
ignoring my instructions.

662
00:54:10,311 --> 00:54:12,680
And now, you're playing pranks?

663
00:54:17,919 --> 00:54:19,850
That's enough!

664
00:54:20,302 --> 00:54:23,997
Yoo Jin, now that I'm here..

665
00:54:24,806 --> 00:54:26,175
step down please.

666
00:54:26,175 --> 00:54:29,077
- Professor, I still have one day...
- Please step down.

667
00:54:41,698 --> 00:54:47,030
Let's change the mood now
and start from the beginning.

668
00:54:48,622 --> 00:54:52,789
Yoo Il Lak? Don't focus on
your bowing, just enjoy yourself.

669
00:54:52,789 --> 00:54:54,623
Your usual soulfulness.

670
00:54:54,623 --> 00:54:55,754
Yes, sir.

671
00:54:55,754 --> 00:54:57,508
Second horn!

672
00:54:58,626 --> 00:55:00,494
You have a cold.

673
00:55:01,134 --> 00:55:03,778
Don't play it too hard today.

674
00:55:03,778 --> 00:55:05,137
Got it!

675
00:55:05,556 --> 00:55:10,219
Clarinet... you should change that reed.

676
00:55:10,219 --> 00:55:11,868
Yes, Professor.

677
00:55:12,427 --> 00:55:14,328
Miss Viola...

678
00:55:14,863 --> 00:55:17,985
Please fall hard for me, too.

679
00:55:17,985 --> 00:55:20,721
You're not my type, Professor.

680
00:55:29,329 --> 00:55:36,277
Beethoven composed Eroica
to offer it to Napoleon.

681
00:55:36,277 --> 00:55:42,259
But Napoleon changed from

682
00:55:42,259 --> 00:55:44,219
a revolutionary to a tyrant.

683
00:55:44,219 --> 00:55:50,458
As soon as Beethoven heard it,
he changed the title to 'Eroica.'

684
00:55:50,934 --> 00:55:54,605
He unknowingly decided to create

685
00:55:54,605 --> 00:55:59,643
his own revolution through music.

686
00:56:05,157 --> 00:56:08,326
Let's start our Eroica!

687
00:56:19,171 --> 00:56:23,491
It's still messy but it's different.

688
00:56:23,491 --> 00:56:25,852
They are making a different sound.

689
00:56:25,852 --> 00:56:30,049
Just because he's up there..

690
00:56:45,322 --> 00:56:49,812
He is... truly a maestro.

691
00:56:57,626 --> 00:57:02,091
It's fair to judge
from the Autumn performance?

692
00:57:02,543 --> 00:57:05,500
One school with two orchestras?

693
00:57:05,500 --> 00:57:08,554
It'll create tension between students.

694
00:57:08,554 --> 00:57:12,517
Disassembling one will be
the best for the all of us.

695
00:57:20,482 --> 00:57:22,984
It's game over now.

696
00:57:25,195 --> 00:57:28,965
Yoo Jin, you have failed.

697
00:57:36,790 --> 00:57:40,290
I denounce you as the assistant conductor.

698
00:57:40,290 --> 00:57:43,305
Please leave now...

699
00:57:43,305 --> 00:57:45,549
From my orchestra.

700
00:57:52,006 --> 00:57:53,540
I don't want to.

701
00:57:54,641 --> 00:57:59,245
You said you'd give me
until tomorrow.

702
00:58:02,056 --> 00:58:03,954
Until tomorrow...

703
00:58:06,111 --> 00:58:07,988
This is my orchestra.

704
00:58:53,158 --> 00:58:55,185
Yes, we have Yoo Jin!

705
00:58:55,185 --> 00:58:57,512
Be a conductor!

706
00:58:57,512 --> 00:59:00,316
Congratulations! Congratulations!

707
00:59:00,316 --> 00:59:02,751
You think I should be
congratulated now?

708
00:59:03,252 --> 00:59:05,128
Why? You think I'll lose?

709
00:59:05,128 --> 00:59:06,505
Why don't we have a battle?

710
00:59:06,505 --> 00:59:08,741
We're going to separate for a while!

711
00:59:08,741 --> 00:59:11,413
What a complete mess...

712
00:59:11,413 --> 00:59:13,282
Fine, Yoo Jin!

713
00:59:13,282 --> 00:59:15,986
If he's hated that much,
he's disqualified as a conductor.

714
00:59:15,986 --> 00:59:17,446
A battle of performances.

715
00:59:17,446 --> 00:59:20,682
The team that loses will be disbanded.
